        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I think it may have more to do than just the clipping plane.  I had noted in another thread that after the patch, whenever I switched to book view (or "interface" mode as opposed to full screen mode) the black around the game screen would flash like a strobe light between black and the last image of the environment around me.  As well, the non-3D parts of this screen would "decay" and smudge until it was a horrible mess, then clear up and do it all over again.  However, this did NOT happen if I turned off Full Screen Anti Aliasing.  It worked perfectly before the patch, afterwards it's all messed up.  I also noticed the clip plane thing too...</P><P><table><td><BR><font size=1><BR>Zerfall<BR>Gnomish Purveyor of Death and Pestilence</P><P>I have not the need of agents and underlings,<BR>for I am Death...<BR></font id=size1><BR></td></table><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
